==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[galingal]], from Arabic {{ARchar|[[قالنجان]]}} (qālanjān) (cognate with Persian {{FAchar|[[قولنجان]]}} (kūlinjān), Sanskrit [[कुलञ्जन]]), perhaps from Chinese ''gāoliángjiāng'', from ''gāoliáng'' (a district in China) + [[薑]] (jiāng) ‘ginger’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'gælɪŋgeɪl/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|galingale|galingales}}
# any of several east Asian plants of the [[ginger]] family, used as a spice

